  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "+WFIIFB2N5ga5Mx/qzWMVFcm6P4=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:33.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Pattern\n\nSharing a document through chat composes three existing primitives \u2014 no new protocol:\n\n1. **Share bundle** \u2014 the existing `shareDocuments(docIds, recipientAddress)` creates the ACT-protected bundle on Swarm.\n2. **Chat message** \u2014 a PSS message of type `share` carries a `DocumentShareAttachment` with the bundle's Swarm reference + a human-readable document list.\n3. **GSOC notification** \u2014 a ping to the recipient's notify signer so their UI refreshes immediately rather than on next poll.\n\n## Payload shape\n\n```typescript\n{\n  type: \"share\",\n  text: \"Check out this invoice\",\n  timestamp: \"2026-04-15T18:30:00Z\",\n  attachment: {\n    kind: \"document-share\",\n    driveId: \"96ffdf26-...\",\n    driveName: \"Q1 Invoices\",\n    shareReference: \"abc123...\",\n    documents: [\n      { id: \"b9e4fe2e-...\", name: \"Invoice #42\", type: \"powerhouse/document-model\" }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Adapter surface\n\nThe unified `buildDriveShareBundle()` in `plugin/sharing.ts` is shared between the Settings share panel and the chat share picker (`document-share-picker.tsx`). Both produce the same bundle shape and preserve sender signatures on every op \u2014 full parity with the Settings path.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:33.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:33.000Z"
    }
  },
